Feeling overwhelmed by the constant need to meet expectationsboth internal and external. #ExpectationPressure
Struggling with emotional instability and frequent mood swings. #EmotionalInstability
Feeling a sense of shame or embarrassment about one's depression. #Stigma
Feeling a sense of disconnection from your own identity or sense of self. #IdentityLoss
Feeling unsupported or invalidated by family members who dismiss my depression as a temporary phase. #LackOfFamilySupport
Feeling restless or agitated, unable to find peace or calmness. #Restlessness
Having difficulty in focusing or concentrating on tasks. #DifficultyConcentrating
Experiencing physical symptoms such as headaches, stomachaches, or muscle tension. #PhysicalSymptoms
It's hard to find solace in a world that feels so cruel.
"I struggle with recurring thoughts of death or dying, as if it's the only way to escape this pain."
Having difficulty in managing everyday tasks and responsibilities. #FunctionalImpairment
Feeling a sense of disconnection from personal aspirations or a lack of motivation to pursue them. #LackOfAspiration

Social interactions have become a source of anxiety and discomfort. The mere thought of engaging with others fills me with a sense of dread. I retreat into solitude, seeking solace in the familiarity of isolation, even though it only exacerbates the loneliness.
It's a constant battle to maintain a semblance of motivation. Some days, I can barely find the strength to get out of bed. #MotivationalStruggles
